---
import TrustLayout from '../../layouts/TrustLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../../data/site';
const title = 'Contact | Utilitas';
const description = 'Where to send project feedback, accessibility reports, corrections, and security concerns for Utilitas tools.';
---

<TrustLayout title={title} description={description} path="/contact/" eyebrow="Get in touch">
  <h2>Choose the closest route</h2>
  <p>Feedback is easiest to evaluate when it reaches the project it concerns. Include the product name, affected URL, browser and device when relevant, what you expected, and what happened.</p>

  <div class="contact-options">
    <section>
      <h3>SVG Vector Lab</h3>
      <p>Use the project's maintained contact page for editor feedback, SVG problems, corrections, and accessibility reports.</p>
      <a class="text-link" href="https://svgvectorlab.com/contact/">SVG Vector Lab contact <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h3>Utilitas and upcoming projects</h3>
      <p>Use the public maintainer profile for repository questions and general project coordination. Do not post secrets or private files in a public issue.</p>
      <a class="text-link" href={SITE.ownerUrl}>Maintainer on GitHub <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
    </section>
  </div>

  <h2>Security and privacy reports</h2>
  <p>For security concerns, look for private vulnerability reporting on the relevant repository or project security page before opening a public issue. For privacy questions, describe the affected site and data flow without including unnecessary personal information.</p>

  <h2>No public intake form</h2>
  <p>This hub deliberately avoids a contact form so it does not need to collect, store, or route message data. A verified dedicated address can be added later if the collection needs a private general-purpose contact channel.</p>
</TrustLayout>
